===Etymology===
''Tippity'' refers to ''tipping'' meaning touching the ball (with the bat in this case).
===Noun===
# {{cricket}} A form of [[backyard cricket]], or a rule in that, where the [[batsman]] must run if he or she hits the ball.  In normal [[cricket]] the batsman chooses whether to run or not, but forcing a run creates [[run out|runout]] chances and hence more excitement.